column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/97c92f6f1b87c6637fa7e19599b5a45005741990 for binaries and test log.\n
This adds a parameter "--param ssp-buffer-size=1". How does that help compilation when other params are added?\n
Some time ago I wanted to add this switch, but Gavin told me the -all includes this. Perhaps this pull is based on an old version of my pull-request?\n
It's based on 0.7.2, not git. in current HEAD the option is not there. The error I described occurs with 0.7.2 and probably other older releases.\n
Ok, if it's already solved then I'm closing this pull\n
So master does NOT have the overall problem, correct?\n
That's what I understood, as there are no --params in master, they also can't interfere with other options.\n
